Dose reductions due to hematologic toxicity were allowed for fluorouracil and cyclophosphamide , but were not permitted for doxorubicin or DZR . 
Dose reductions for other toxicities were not permitted . 
A dose delay was defined as a period of at least 28 days since the previous cycle of treatment . 
The studies had no predetermined cumulative dose for discontinuation of doxorublcin . 
There was no predetermined cumulative stopping dose of doxorubicin .
